The paper deals with the problem of robot bin picking, which is a common application in robotics and automation. The paper proposes an algorithm that optimizes the motion planning of a robot by incorporating candidate grasps produced by a grasp planner. This involves analyzing the mechanical limits of the robot and avoiding obstacles. Therefore, the paper is likely to belong to the Robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of grasp-analysis tools such as Dex-Net, which suggests that the paper may also belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also involves optimization techniques, which could place it in the Machine Learning (cs.LG) or Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Finally, the paper deals with the dynamics of the robot, which could place it in the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category.
